randoop.types

Class GeneralType

  • java.lang.Object
    • randoop.types.GeneralType
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    ConcreteType, GenericType

    public abstract class GeneralType
extends java.lang.Object
    Common superclass representing types in Randoop. Intended as glue for dealing with generating objects from java.lang.reflect.Type objects, especially instances of java.lang.reflect.ParameterizedType that can either represent generic classes or a parameterized type.

    This class is package private because it should not be necessary to use the class directly within Randoop. The intent is that Randoop will only use the subclasses ConcreteType and GenericType. Instances of GenericType are only be used during harvesting of classes under test using reflection, then these are instantiated to instances of ConcreteType that are then used to generate the tests.

    See Also:
    ConcreteType, GenericType

      • forType

        public static GeneralType forType(java.lang.reflect.Type type)
                           throws RandoopTypeException
        Returns a type constructed from an object hiding behind a java.lang.reflect.Type reference. If the object is a Class instance then returns the corresponding ConcreteType. If the type is actually a java.lang.reflect.ParameterizedType, then the type arguments are inspected to decide whether to return a ParameterizedType or a GenericClassType. If the type is a java.lang.reflect.GenericArrayType, then the corresponding GenericArrayType is returned.

        Note that when the type corresponds to a generic class type, this method returns the type variables from the getActualTypeArguments() method to maintain the guarantees needed for ParameterizedType.isSubtypeOf(ConcreteType).

        Parameters:
        type - the type to interpret
        Returns:
        a randoop.types.Type object corresponding to the given type
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if the rawtype is not a Class instance
        RandoopTypeException
